  "body": "VIP: 1003 \r\nTitle: Modify public variable syntax\r\nAuthor: @MohamedLEGH\r\nType: Standard\r\nStatus: Draft\r\nCreated: 2018-08-20\r\n\r\n## Simple Summary\r\n\r\nChange public getter syntax from:\r\n```\r\nmyVar: public(type)\r\nmyVar2: public(type)\r\n\r\nmyVar3: type\r\n```\r\n\r\nto\r\n```\r\npublic:\r\n  myVar: type\r\n  myVar2: type\r\n\r\nprivate:\r\n  myVar3: type\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo have a more simple style\r\n\r\n## Abstract\r\nI don't like the current public variable syntax.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nAlmost same idea as https://github.com/ethereum/vyper/issues/931\r\n\r\nI think it's better to group public variables together and private variables together. Forcing to explicit which variable is private or public can help visibility and help to avoid errors.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nNew syntax (C++ OO style)\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nNot backwards compatible, user breaking change.\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
