    "body": "@jacqueswww I agree with you that using ```public()``` is not the worst way but I think we can find a better solution.\r\n\r\nIf we don't want to break the python syntax do we have other options ?\r\n\r\nFor example\r\n\r\nSolution 1:\r\n\r\nTo only have private function and force users to write getter\r\n```\r\nmyVar: type\r\n\r\ndef get_myVar():\r\n  return myVar\r\n```\r\n\r\nSolution 2:\r\n\r\nTo create 2 function and init/declare variables inside \r\n```\r\ndef __public__():\r\n  myVar: type\r\n  myVar2: type\r\n\r\ndef __private__():\r\n  myVar3: type\r\n\r\n```",
